<div class="notice">
  <h2>üéâ SpotMenu 2.0 is Here!</h2>
  <p><strong>SpotMenu has been completely rebuilt from the ground up with SwiftUI!</strong></p>
  <p>This is a major update that requires a fresh download. Automatic updates are not available for this transition.</p>
  <a href="https://kmikiy.github.io/SpotMenu/" class="download-btn">Download SpotMenu 2.0 ‚Üí</a>
</div>

<div class="features">
  <h3>What's New in 2.0</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Complete SwiftUI Rebuild</strong> - Native, modern, and beautiful</li>
    <li><strong>New Playback Panel</strong> - Hover over the menu bar to reveal album art and controls</li>
    <li><strong>Track Liking</strong> - Like/unlike tracks directly from the menu bar (Spotify)</li>
    <li><strong>Customizable Appearance</strong> - Blur intensity, tint colors, font weights</li>
    <li><strong>Compact View</strong> - Optional 2-line display mode</li>
    <li><strong>Global Keyboard Shortcuts</strong> - Control playback from anywhere</li>
    <li><strong>Audiobook & Podcast Support</strong> - Display chapter/episode information</li>
    <li><strong>Automatic Updates</strong> - Future updates will install automatically</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>How to Update</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Quit the current SpotMenu</li>
    <li>Download SpotMenu 2.0 from <a href="https://kmikiy.github.io/SpotMenu/">kmikiy.github.io/SpotMenu</a></li>
    <li>Move the new SpotMenu to your Applications folder (replace the old one)</li>
    <li>Launch SpotMenu 2.0 and enjoy!</li>
  </ol>

  <p><em>Thank you for using SpotMenu! ‚ù§Ô∏è</em></p>
</div>
